on the way back.

760
01:19:24,729 --> 01:19:26,855
We're going to do it.

761
01:19:29,150 --> 01:19:31,193
I thought you should know.

762
01:19:34,197 --> 01:19:36,073
You're going to apply?

763
01:19:38,826 --> 01:19:40,201
Yes.

764
01:19:45,958 --> 01:19:47,375
Good.

765
01:21:50,495 --> 01:21:52,371
Madame?

766
01:21:57,669 --> 01:21:59,086
Sorry.

767
01:21:59,963 --> 01:22:02,172
We didn't mean
to startle you.

768
01:22:02,840 --> 01:22:04,591
We were at Hailsham.

769
01:22:09,347 --> 01:22:11,682
I'm Kathy.
This is Tommy.

770
01:22:14,185 --> 01:22:16,519
We're not here to
give you any trouble.

771
01:22:19,982 --> 01:22:21,440
From Hailsham?

772
01:22:21,525 --> 01:22:23,067
We just came
to talk to you.

773
01:22:24,945 --> 01:22:27,196
And I brought you
some things.

774
01:22:28,198 --> 01:22:31,075
Some things you might
like for your Gallery.

775
01:22:33,245 --> 01:22:34,829
Come inside.

776
01:23:10,323 --> 01:23:12,324
Please, wait here.

777
01:23:30,425 --> 01:23:32,217
Look, it's Hailsham.

778
01:23:33,928 --> 01:23:36,096
Kathy, it's Hailsham.

779
01:23:38,058 --> 01:23:40,768
That's exactly
how I remember it.

780
01:23:47,859 --> 01:23:49,484
Please, sit down.

781
01:24:04,792 --> 01:24:06,167
So...

782
01:24:09,380 --> 01:24:10,880
We're in love.

783
01:24:11,674 --> 01:24:14,217
And it's true love.
It's verifiable.

784
01:24:15,302 --> 01:24:17,303
Verifiable. I see.

785
01:24:23,351 --> 01:24:24,851
Go on.

786
01:24:25,103 --> 01:24:26,520
Well,

787
01:24:28,189 --> 01:24:30,816
we'd heard about
the deferrals.

788
01:24:33,027 --> 01:24:35,779
And we'd worked out the
purpose of The Gallery.

789
01:24:37,156 --> 01:24:38,907
Tell me the purpose.

790
01:24:40,702 --> 01:24:43,787
To use our art
from Hailsham

791
01:24:43,996 --> 01:24:46,331
to look into
our souls,

792
01:24:47,375 --> 01:24:50,794
which would verify that
we deserved a deferral.

793
01:24:51,504 --> 01:24:54,880
But the problem is

794
01:24:54,965 --> 01:24:57,842
I was a little bit
mixed up back then

795
01:24:57,926 --> 01:25:02,138
and I didn't
really do any art,

796
01:25:03,807 --> 01:25:06,142
so you never took
anything of mine.

797
01:25:06,226 --> 01:25:09,687
I know, I know that
that is my fault

798
01:25:09,771 --> 01:25:12,982
and it is probably
much too late,

799
01:25:13,066 --> 01:25:15,067
but I brought some stuff with me today.

800
01:25:21,032 --> 01:25:24,117
This is a book
of stuff and...

801
01:25:36,213 --> 01:25:38,256
Other stuff here.

802
01:25:43,053 --> 01:25:46,181
Some of them I've done
quite recently,

803
01:25:47,224 --> 01:25:48,558
and others

804
01:25:50,519 --> 01:25:53,396
were done several years ago,
so there's a real spread.

805
01:25:54,690 --> 01:25:57,983
You already have a load
of stuff from Kath already.

806
01:25:58,067 --> 01:26:01,111
She got loads of stuff into The
Gallery over the years, didn't...

807
01:26:01,237 --> 01:26:02,905
I'm sorry.

808
01:26:06,242 --> 01:26:08,202
I never know
what to do.

809
01:26:15,043 --> 01:26:16,919
I'll take it
from here.

810
01:26:22,801 --> 01:26:24,468
Thank you, George.

811
01:26:28,931 --> 01:26:31,349
Kathy H and Tommy D.

812
01:26:33,101 --> 01:26:35,061
I remember you both.

813
01:26:35,604 --> 01:26:38,731
Kathy, a bright girl,
and so creative.

814
01:26:39,024 --> 01:26:42,318
And Tommy, a big heart
and terrible rages.

815
01:26:46,573 --> 01:26:48,282
You have to understand,

816
01:26:49,284 --> 01:26:53,871
Hailsham was the last place to
consider the ethics of donation.

817
01:26:54,289 --> 01:26:57,667
We used your art to show
what you were capable of.

818
01:26:58,334 --> 01:27:01,002
To show that donor children
are all but human.

819
01:27:02,839 --> 01:27:06,800
But we were providing an answer
to a question no one was asking.

820
01:27:08,386 --> 01:27:10,595
If you ask people
to return to darkness,

821
01:27:10,680 --> 01:27:15,183
the days of lung cancer, breast
cancer, motor neurone disease,

822
01:27:16,143 --> 01:27:18,019
they'll simply say no.

823
01:27:21,399 --> 01:27:24,693
We used to get two or three
couples like you a year.

824
01:27:26,320 --> 01:27:28,238
Not so much these days.

825
01:27:29,739 --> 01:27:32,241
You're the first
for quite a while.

826
01:27:36,371 --> 01:27:38,664
To apply
for a deferral?

827
01:27:47,090 --> 01:27:49,508
There are
no deferrals, Tommy.

828
01:27:54,514 --> 01:27:58,726
There are no deferrals.
And there never have been.

829
01:28:09,194 --> 01:28:12,947
We didn't have The Gallery in
order to look into your souls.

830
01:28:13,365 --> 01:28:16,576
We had The Gallery to see
if you had souls at all.

831
01:28:29,632 --> 01:28:31,299
Do you understand?

832
01:28:42,185 --> 01:28:43,560
Yes.

833
01:28:50,401 --> 01:28:53,236
Your drawings
are very good.

834
01:28:54,572 --> 01:28:57,074
If you want,
I'll keep them.

835
01:29:59,510 --> 01:30:01,636
Thank you
for talking to us.

836
01:30:05,474 --> 01:30:07,224
You poor creatures.

837
01:30:09,019 --> 01:30:10,978
I wish I could help you.

838
01:31:10,912 --> 01:31:13,538
Sorry, can we stop for a
second? I need to get out.

839
01:34:21,346 --> 01:34:23,931
It's been two weeks
since I lost him.

840
01:34:54,545 --> 01:34:56,754
I've been given my notice now.

841
01:35:00,592 --> 01:35:03,261
My first donation
is in a month's time.

842
01:35:11,937 --> 01:35:15,189
I come here and imagine
that this is the spot

843
01:35:15,274 --> 01:35:19,193
where everything I've lost
since my childhood has washed up.

844
01:35:23,156 --> 01:35:26,491
I tell myself
if that were true,

845
01:35:27,327 --> 01:35:29,661
and I waited long enough,

846
01:35:30,747 --> 01:35:34,624
then a tiny figure would appear
on the horizon across the field

847
01:35:34,792 --> 01:35:38,754
and gradually get larger
until I'd see it was Tommy.

848
01:35:41,799 --> 01:35:43,383
He'd wave

849
01:35:43,843 --> 01:35:45,719
and maybe call.

850
01:35:48,056 --> 01:35:51,099
I don't let the fantasy
go beyond that.

851
01:35:51,309 --> 01:35:52,642
I can't let it.

852
01:35:54,770 --> 01:35:58,773
I remind myself I was lucky to
have had any time with him at all.

853
01:36:03,320 --> 01:36:05,571
What I'm not sure about

854
01:36:06,073 --> 01:36:10,659
is if our lives have been so different
from the lives of the people we save.

855
01:36:13,622 --> 01:36:15,539
We all complete.

856
01:36:18,001 --> 01:36:21,712
Maybe none of us really
understand what we've lived through

857
01:36:23,673 --> 01:36:26,216
or feel we've had
enough time.

858
01:42:49,254 --> 01:42:54,675
When we are scattered
afar and asunder

859
01:42:55,010 --> 01:43:00,222
Parted are those
who are singing today

860
01:43:00,807 --> 01:43:06,437
When we look back
and forgetfully wonder

861
01:43:06,938 --> 01:43:12,401
What we were like
in our learning and play

862
01:43:12,819 --> 01:43:18,323
Oh, the great days
will bring distance enchanted

863
01:43:18,574 --> 01:43:23,661
Days of fresh air
in the rain and the sun

864
01:43:24,205 --> 01:43:29,542
How we rejoiced
as we struggled and panted

865
01:43:30,002 --> 01:43:36,966
Echoes of dreamland,
Hailsham lives on

